headline: Stock Market Today: Dow Scores Record In Face Of Shutdown Risk; Nvidia Breaks Out (Live Coverage)
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average and other major stock indexes ended Tuesday on a high note, even as investors awaited word on a Washington spending bill that could stave off a partial government shutdown at midnight.  Downbeat consumer confidence data had dampened investors' mood, but indexes eventually escaped losses.  On the stock market today, Spotify slid while Nvidia hit a new high.

headline: IBM Stock Gains on Quantum Optimism. This Analyst Isn’t Convinced.
summary: International Business Machines  caused shock waves last week after it shared the results of a quantum-powered bond-trading experiment conducted with HSBC, but one analyst is questioning whether the news was overplayed.  The results, reached in collaboration with Vanguard, indicated that quantum computers could work with classical machines to deliver results on par with purely classical methods.  IBM shares barely reacted to the news in early trading Tuesday, a contrast to the jump that occurred after the HSBC experiment was unveiled on Thursday.

headline: IBM, Vanguard Tap Quantum to Optimize Portfolios
summary: Paul Malloy, head of munis at Vanguard, and Scott Crowder, VP of quantum adoption at IBM, tell Romaine Bostick and Katie Greifeld on "The Close" that IBM and Vanguard are exploring quantum optimization for portfolio construction. They say the technology is advancing now because quantum computers can run programs that can't be simulated classically, opening new ways to explore investment strategies.
